snippet.textDisplay: Youngest ever squad in Liverpool's history and the boys did us proud! Nearly full capacity at Anfield and amazing support as always for the team by the fans (even Man City cant seem to achieve that for a CL match at Emptyhad) Crazy knowing how this squad is only 19 years old on average. Boys played like men and men played like boys! We were clearly the better side and they said we disrespected the FA CUP... Great game by the boys and Shrewsbury were more of a threat than everton's first team. Still undefeated in Anfield (despite playing our U19s) and the record keeps on growing! Hope the boys got to bed early for school. We Go Again #YNWA
